@@TJvTipOfDay.LoadFromFile
Summary
  Fills the tip list with the lines of text in a specified file.
Description
  Call LoadFromFile to fill the list Tips from the file specified by FileName. Each line in the file,
  as indicated by carriage return or linefeed characters, is appended as a string in the list.
Parameters
  AFileName - Name of the file where to read the tips from..
See Also
  <LINK SaveToFile>, Tips
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTipOfDay.OnAfterExecute
Summary
  Occurs after the dialog is closed.
Description
  \Write an OnAfterExecute handler to store the value that determines whether the dialog must be shown
  the next time the application starts up.
  
  A user can uncheck the checkbox on the dialog to indicate that the dialog must not be shown the next
  time the application starts up. The dialog provides a built-in method to store this value, that uses the
  registry. However, applications can provide a custom method to store this value.
  
  The flag toShowOnStartUp in Options indicates whether the checkbox was checked or unchecked, when the
  user closed the dialog. If toShowOnStartUp is included in Options then the checkbox was checked,
  otherwise it was unchecked.
  
  Use a OnCanShow event handler to retrieve the stored value and to determine whether the dialog can be shown.
See Also
  Execute, OnCanShow, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTipOfDay.OnCanShow
Summary
  Occurs before the dialog is shown.
Description
  \Write an OnCanShow event handler to provide a custom check whether the Tip of the Day dialog can
  be shown. The dialog provides a built-in check, that uses the registry to determine whether the
  dialog can be shown. This check can be used by including the flag toShowOnStartUp in Options.
  However, applications can provide custom checks in an OnCanShow event handler. 

  Set the CanShow parameter to False to prevent the dialog from showing. 
Parameters
  Sender  - The tip dialog that fired the event
  CanShow - Determines whether the tip dialog can be shown.
See Also
  Execute, OnAfterExecute
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTipOfDay.Options
Summary
  Specifies options for the dialog.
Description
  Use the Options property to customize the functionality of the dialog. Use these flags to specify:
  
  * Whether the dialog should be shown on start-up.
  * Whether the dialog should use the registry to store the value of the "Show \Tips on StartUp" checkbox.
See Also
  Execute
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTipOfDay.SaveToFile
Summary
  Saves the tips list to the specified file.
Description
  Call SaveToFile to save the tips in the list Tips to the file specified by FileName. Each string in
  the list is written to a separate line in the file.
Parameters
  AFileName - Name of the file where to write the tips to.
See Also
  <LINK LoadFromFile>, Tips
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTipOfDay.Style
Summary
